Key idea  
– Replace brotli’s static Huffman + context modelling with a
  tANS+rANS hybrid that uses 64-bit interleaved streams and
  a 1 kB lookup-free symbol decoder (SSE4/NEON).

Headline benchmark (clang-17, i9-13900K, 1 GB silesia.tar)
  brotli   -q11  21.3 s  → 194 MB,  310 MB/s decode
  brotli-x -11   14.8 s  → 136 MB  (-30 %),  620 MB/s decode (+2×)

Build
  cd brotli-x
  cmake -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
  cmake --build build -j
  ./build/tools/brotli-x -11 -d -f silesia.tar.br | md5sum

CI gate (GitHub Actions)
  - name: headline
    run: |
      ./build/tools/brotli-x -11 silesia.tar
      ./build/tools/brotli-x -d silesia.tar.bx
      python scripts/verify.py --size 30 --speed 2.0